I want to ask you as we reflect this morning, what in your life right now does God reveal

57:49.698 --> 58:01.097
that you need to put to death, mortify as a Puritan saying, and are you believing and trusting Jesus Christ?

58:02.419 --> 58:05.605
Is ever sinful and imperfect as your life can be?

58:05.625 --> 58:09.591
Is he the one to whom you look?

58:09.611 --> 58:10.873
Do you need him this morning?

58:13.578 --> 58:16.082
I remember backward what he did

58:16.194 --> 58:27.528
fulfilling all of those sacrifices, renew upward as you look to Him, reflect inward to ensure that we're seeking to glorify Him and enjoy Him forever.

58:27.848 --> 58:35.738
Reach around so that we are one together with those in the church and then we rejoice.

58:37.520 --> 58:38.261
Let's pray together.

58:42.025 --> 58:45.970
Father, we come before you, the glory of heaven.

58:47.106 --> 58:58.844
who is stooped so low to love sinners such as us and to show all of your covenant promises are sure and that you are with us through this tangible sign.

59:01.127 --> 59:13.586
Father, we take this bread, we take this cup before you and we ask for your blessing, your sanctifying presence as we give thanksgiving to you.

59:14.722 --> 59:22.915
And we pray that we would feast on you, and we pray that you would do a wonderful work of grace within us.

59:25.058 --> 59:32.930
We thank you for reconciling us to yourself, and we pray that you would unite us more to you through this time.

59:34.693 --> 59:37.357
We confess you as Lord, and we love it so.

59:38.478 --> 59:40.882
In Jesus' name we pray, amen.

